turnkey-ansible-13.0-beta2 (1) turnkey; urgency=low

   - Updated to Ansible 1.6.6
   - Added python-setuptools now required by Ansible

 -- John Carver <dude4linux@gmail.com>  Sat Jul 12 17:58:48 UTC 2014

 * Ansible Appliance:

   - Ansible is an IT automation tool. It can configure systems, deploy software,
     and orchestrate more advanced IT tasks such as continuous deployments
     or zero downtime rolling updates.

   - Latest stable version of Ansible is installed via git at build time.
   - No server or client daemons; uses existing SSHd
   - No additional software required on clients
   - Modules can be written in ANY language
   - Does not require root privledges
   
   * Special notes about TurnKey Ansible appliance
   - Login as user 'ansible' to run Ansible
   - Login as user 'root' to manage server

 * Please refer to turnkey-core's changelog for changes common to all
    appliances, as well as the following git logs:
    
    - https://github.com/turnkeylinux/common
    - https://github.com/turnkeylinux-apps/drupal7

 -- John Carver <dude4linux@gmail.com>  Sun, 29 Dec 2013 16:50:01 -0600
